    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A type of mixed lace consisting of a light ground in mechanically produced tulle on which motifs are applied in bobbin- or needle lace. These motifs may be floral or figural. The technique was common from the mid-18th century and throughout the 19th.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
